#!/usr/bin/env bash
VERSION='v1.4.4'

narada-remote "rm var/patch/$(cat config/version).$USER.* 2>/dev/null"
narada-upload var/patch/$(cat config/version).$USER.*        &&
narada-remote -t "narada-lock-exclusive narada-patch --no-prev" # --no-prev for compatibility with <0.9.3

exit
: <<'=cut'

=encoding utf8

=head1 NAME

narada-patch-remote - upload latests patch files and apply patch on remote side


=head1 VERSION

This document describes narada-patch-remote version v1.4.4


=head1 USAGE

    narada-patch-remote


=head1 DESCRIPTION

Script must be executed only from "project root directory".

Narada must be installed on remote side too.


=head1 REQUIRED ARGUMENTS

None.


=head1 OPTIONS

See USAGE.


=head1 DIAGNOSTICS

None.


=head1 CONFIGURATION AND ENVIRONMENT

config/remote


=head1 DEPENDENCIES

None.


=head1 INCOMPATIBILITIES

None reported.


=head1 BUGS AND LIMITATIONS

No bugs have been reported.

Please report any bugs or feature requests to
C<bug-narada@rt.cpan.org>, or through the web interface at
L<http://rt.cpan.org>.


